NCCP
Saskatoon YMCA Tournament
April 4, 2009

A big thank you to all of those who helped making our tournament a big success this past weekend.
Without people like T.V. Taylor, Darrell Brown, Bernadette Leuschen, Bev Yuen and the many others who volunteered their time, the tournament would not have run as smooth as it did.
A special thanks must also go out to Eric Langdon from Moose Jaw who delivered the mats to Saskatoon on Friday evening.
Without these special people involved in our sport we would truly struggle at putting on tournaments of this size and have them run so smooth!
Thanks, John Schatz, President of the Saskatoon YMCA Judo Club
